summary:
An experienced multilingual researcher, writer, and international affairs specialist, with a particular interest in agricultural and societal policy.

I have lived in South Korea for 5+ years. During this time, I have finished my Master's of International Studies at Seoul National University and started my professional career with a special focus on communication and startups. 

With a passion for research and communication, I have gained strengths in the fields of research, journalism, policy analysis, writing & editing. Always aiming to enhance my communication skills, I am currently working on gaining professional proficiency in Korean and German.
